                                        ============================
                                        :     File Handling        :
                                        ============================

-> Very important are in every programming language.
-> Below are the common file operations in the project.

1. Create a file
2. Write the data to file 
3. Read the data from file
4. Delete the file

--> To perform file operations java language provided one predefined class java.io.File
--> java.io package contains set of classes and interfaces to perform input and output operations.

                    File f = new File( String name );

--> We have several methods in the file class.

createNewFile(); --> It is used to create a new empty file.
mkdir(); ---> It is used to create new empty directory.
delete(); --> It is used to delete the file / directory based on given name.
isFile(); ---> It is used to check weather it is a file or not.
isDirectory(); ---> It is used to check weather it is a directory or not.

Example: 
========

package com.ibm.aadhar;

import java.io.File;
import java.io.IOException;

public class test {
	
	public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
		
		File f = new File("abc.txt");
		boolean fstatus = f.createNewFile();
		System.out.println(fstatus);
		
		
		File f1 = new File("sonu.txt");
		boolean f1status = f1.createNewFile();
		System.out.println(f1status);
		
		File f2 = new File("WorkSpaceByFileCreation");
		boolean f2status = f2.mkdir( );
		System.out.println(f2status);
		
		File f3 = new File("WorkSpaceByFileCreation", "siba");
		boolean f3status = f3.createNewFile();
		System.out.println(f3status);
	}

}



