                                    ==================================================
                                                  FILE OPERATIONS (O/I Streams)
                                    ==================================================

-> To perform operations on the file we need to use I/O streams.
-> Using I/O streams we can establish link between java program and file(physical file).

java program <---- write ----> file
java program <---- read  ----> file


I/O streams devided into 2 types.

1. Byte Stream: To read/write Binary data (images, audios, videos, pdf etc)...
2.Characters Stream: To read/write character data(text file).

-> Byte stream is providing 2 types of classes.

        1.InputStream related classes(Ex: FileInputStream )
        2.OutputStream related classes(Ex: FileOutputStream )
-> Character stream is also providing 2 types of classes.

        1.Reader classes (Ex: FileReader )
        2.Writer classes( Ex: FileWriter )













































